= Chapter 2: Conditions

Conditions are temporary statuses that can be applied to characters. Each condition listed below includes its primary cause and often suggests other possible causes, describes the effect the condition has on a person, and explains how the condition is removed.
== Agony

_Cause:_ When a condition or injury causes you intense, unbearable pain, you are in \[Agony\].

_Effect:_ All skill actions have their DL raised by _two_. Taking painkillers diminishes the effect of \[Agony\]. When you take painkillers, skill actions have their DL raised by one (instead of two).

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be in \[Agony\] is removed, you lose the \[Agony\] condition. If you are in \[Agony\] due to an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the injury's Recovery entry, causes you to lose the \[Agony\] condition.
== Bewildered

_Cause:_ When a skill action, condition, or effect leaves you deeply and utterly confused, you are \[Bewildered\]. This replaces the \[Distracted\] condition.

_Effect:_ You are \[Unaware\].

_Removal:_ At the start of your turn, you lose the \[Bewildered\] condition.
== Bleeding

_Cause:_ When you take damage from an attack that applies this condition, you gain \[Bleeding\].

_Effect:_ At the end of your turn, take 1 damage.

_Removal:_ When you gain the \[Stabilized\] condition, you lose the \[Bleeding\] condition.
== Blinded

_Cause:_ When an attack, condition, or environmental effect prevents you from seeing, you are \[Blinded\]. This condition replaces \[Vision Impairment\].

_Effect:_ You cannot see. All targets have \[Concealment, Total\] from you. \[Ranged\] attacks you make, except for Point Blank Shot, have their DL raised by _two_. Point Blank Shot and \[Melee\] attacks you make have their DL raised by one. You gain \[Movement Restricted\]. All other skill actions with the \[Visual\] keyword have their DL raised by _two_ or may be impossible (GM's discretion).

_Removal:_ When the condition or environmental effect that caused you to be \[Blinded\] is removed, you lose the \[Blinded\] condition. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Break

_Cause:_ When a a person or situation pushes you to your limits, you \[Break\] and can no longer control your behavior.

_Effect:_ You attack, flee, or break down on the stop with an outpouring of emotion (the GM chooses). If you attack, you target what you perceive to be the source of your problems or ire, which could be a person, place, or thing. If you flee, you attempt to escape that perceived source.

_Removal:_ At the start of your turn, make a basic Resilience roll with a DL of Hard (14). Success means you regain control and lose the \[Break\] condition.
== Cognitive Impairment

_Cause:_ When a condition or effect makes it harder for you to think, you have a \[Cognitive Impairment\].

_Effect:_ Skill actions roll with Intellect have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition or effect that caused \[Cognitive Impairment\] is removed, you lose the \[Cognitive Impairment\] condition. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Compliant

_Cause:_ When a person or group is compelled to perform actions under duress, they gain the \[Compliant\] condition. This condition cannot be applied to player characters.

_Effect:_ The Attitude of the \[Compliant\] person or group shifts to Hostile. They follow orders from the person (or people) they fear. They can be instructed to act against their own self-interests, but they will not put their loved ones at risk. They will not attempt to escape or retaliate as long as those they fear remain present.

_Removal:_ Forcing someone to put their loved ones at risk causes them to \[Break\] and lose \[Compliant\]. If a \[Compliant\] person or group is left unattended for a few minutes, they automatically lose the \[Compliant\] condition..
== Concealment, Partial

_Cause:_ You are partly concealed, making it harder for you to be seen by an observer. It is possible to have \[Concealment. Partial\] to one observer and not another.

_Effect:_ Attacks made against you by an observer to whom you have \[Concealment, Partial\] have their DL raised by one. Attempts to locate you through sight alone have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When you become fully visible to an observer or switch to having \[Concealment, Total\] to them, you no longer have \[Concealment. Partial\] to them.
== Concealment, Total

_Cause:_ Your entire body, including your gear, are totally concealed and cannot be seen by an observer. It is possible to have \[Concealment, Total\] to one observer and not another.

_Effect:_ Attacks made against you by an observer to whom you have \[Concealment, Total\] have their D: raised by one. If the attacker's d20 roll (excluding ability score) is _odd_ (1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15, 17, or 19) then the attacker's outcome is downgraded. Attempts made by the observer to locate you through sight alone automatically fail.

_Removal:_ When you become fully visible to an observer or switch to having \[Concealment, Partial\] to them, you no longer have \[Concealment, Total\] to them.
== Critical Condition

_Cause:_ When you have sustained a \[Life Threatening\] injury and were subsequently \[Stabilized\] only to then fail your basic Resilience roll at the start of a scene, you enter \[Critical Condition\]. You can also gain \[Critical Condition\] as the result of Surgery or Cybernetic Installation that ends in critical failure.

_Effect:_ At the end of each hour that passes, relative to you, make a basic Resilience roll with a DL of Severe (18). If you succeed, you gain \[Stabilized\]. If you fail, make a mark. If you accumulate more marks than your Resilience score, you advance to \[Dying\].

_Removal:_ When you gain \[Stabilized\], you lose \[Critical Condition\]. Any marks accumulated from failed basic Resilience rolls are reset to zero.
== Death's Door

_Cause:_ When you are reduced to half your Severely Wounded value (or less) in hit points, you gain the \[Death's Door\] condition. This condition follows and replaces \[Wounded\] and \[Severely Wounded\].

_Effect:_ You gain \[Movement Restricted\]. You are \[Prone\]. All skill actions have their DL raised by one. The first time you gain \[Death's Door\] during a scene, roll on the _Injury Severity Chart_.

_Removal:_ When you have more than half of your Severely Wounded hit points, you lose the \[Death's Door\] condition. You also lose the \[Death's Door\] condition if you advance to \[Dying\].
== Deafened

_Cause:_ When a skill action, condition, or environmental effect prevents you from hearing, you gain the \[Deafened\] condition. This condition replaces \[Hearing Impaired\].

_Effect:_ You cannot hear, or you can only hear one thing (music in a nightclub, for example). You are immune to sound-based attacks. Attempts to use skill actions with the \[Vocal\] quality have their DL raised by one. You are unable to use skill actions that have the \[Auditory\] keyword.

_Removal:_ When the condition of environmental effect that caused you to be \[Deafened\] is removed, you lose the \[Deafened\] condition.
== Disfigured, Major

_Cause:_ When a condition or injury dramatically alters your appearance in an unnatural way, you gain \[Disfigured, Major\]. This condition stacks with itself and with \[Disfigured, Minor\].

_Effect:_ The DL for the following skill actions is raised by _two_: Improve Attitude, Persuade, Bluff, and Blend In. The DL for the Intimidate skill action is  by lowered by _two_.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Disfigured, Major\] is removed, you lose the \[Disfigured, Major\] condition. If you gained \[Disfigured, Major\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Disfigured, Major\].
== Disfigured, Minor

_Cause:_ When a condition or injury alters your appearance in an unnatural way, you gain \[Disfigured, Minor\]. This condition stacks with itself and with \[Disfigured, Major\].

_Effect:_ The DL for the following skill actions is raised by one: Improve Attitude, Persuade, Bluff, and Blend In. The DL for the Intimidate skill action s lowered by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Disfigured, Minor\] is removed, you lose the \[Disfigured, Minor\] condition. If you gained \[Disfigured, Minor\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Disfigured, Minor\].
== Dying

_Cause:_ When you are reduced to 0 hit points, you gain the \[Dying\] condition. This condition follows and replaces \[Healthy\], \[Wounded\], \[Severely Wounded\], and \[Death's Door\].

_Effect:_ You are \[Unconscious\]. Make a mark. At the start of your turn, make a basic Resilience roll with a DL of Hard (14). Success means you gain the \[Stabilized\] condition. Failure means you make another mark. If you accumulate more marks than your Resilience score, you are dead.

_Removal:_ When you gain \[Stabilized\], you lose the \[Dying\] condition. You have 1 hit point.
== Distracted

_Cause:_ When a skill action, condition, or effect causes you to become unfocused and momentarily lose track of what you were doing, you are \[Distracted\].

_Effect:_ You are \[Off Guard\].

_Removal:_ At the start of your turn, you lose the \[Distracted Condition\]. You also lose \[Distracted\] if you are in the presence of danger.
== Fine Motor Impairment

_Cause:_ When you have difficulty doing things that use fine motor control, you have \[Fine Motor Impairment\].

_Effect:_ Skill actions with the \[Fine Control\] keyword have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused \[Fine Motor Impairment\] is removed, you lose the \[Fine Motor Impairment\] condition. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Healthy

_Cause:_ When you have more than half your maximum hit points, you are \[Healthy\].

_Effect:_ You are healthy.

_Removal:_ Lose at least half of your maximum hit points.
== Hearing Impairment

_Cause:_ When you have difficulty hearing due to a condition or effect, you have \[Hearing Impairment\].

_Effect:_ Skill actions with the \[Auditory\] keyword have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused \[Hearing Impairment\] is removed, you lose the \[Hearing Impairment\] condition. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Hidden

_Cause:_ When you successfully use the Hide skill action, you gain the \[Hidden\] condition.

_Effect:_ You are \[Undetected\] and have \[Concealment, Total\].

_Removal:_ When you reveal your position by attacking, stepping out of cover, or making noise, you lose the \[Hidden\] condition.
== Immobilized

_Cause:_ When you gain the \[Unconscious\] condition, you also gain \[Immobilized\]. You can also gain \[Immobilized\] by certain special attacks or by being bound, such as with rope.

_Effect:_ You cannot move.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Immobilized\] is removed, you lose the \[Immobilized\] condition. If you gained \[Immobilized\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Immobilized\].
== Incapable

_Cause:_ When a condition, effect, or injury renders you unable to act, you are \[Incapable\].

_Effect:_ You cannot use skill actions or spend AP.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Incapable\] is removed, you lose the \[Incapable\] condition. If you gained \[Incapable\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Incapable\].
== Life Threatening

_Cause:_ When you sustain an injury that requires emergency treatment, without which you could could die, you have a \[Life Threatening\] condition.

_Effect:_ As determined by the injury you sustained. See _Sustaining an Injury_ for specific effects.

_Removal:_ Receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose the \[Life Threatening\] condition.
== Mouth Breather

_Cause:_ When a condition, effect, or injury prevents you from breathing through your nose, you gain \[Mouth Breather\].

_Effect:_ The DL for the following skill actions is raised by one: Move Silently, Slip Past.

_Removal:_ When you gain the ability to breathe through your nose again, you to lose \[Mouth Breather\].
== Movement Impaired

_Cause:_ When a condition or injury makes it harder to move, you are \[Movement Impaired\].

_Effect:_ When you spend 1 AP to move in combat, use your \[Half-Speed\] (instead of your \[Speed\]).

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Movement Impaired\] is removed, you lose the \[Movement Impaired\] condition. If you gained \[Movement Impaired\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Movement Impaired\].
== Movement Restricted

_Cause:_ When a condition or injury makes it nearly impossible to move, you are \[Movement Restricted\]. This condition replaces \[Movement Impaired\].

_Effect:_ When you spend 1 AP to move in combat, you can move only 1 meter, usually by crawling. You cannot use Athletics skill actions.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Movement Restricted\] is removed, you lose the \[Movement Restricted\] condition. If you gained \[Movement Restricted\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Movement Restricted\].
== Muted

_Cause:_ When a condition, effect, or injury prevents you from speaking, you are \[Muted\]. This condition replaces \[Speech Impairment\].

_Effect:_ You cannot speak, though you may be able to make grunts and other sounds. You cannot use skill actions with the \[Vocal\] keyword.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Muted\] is removed, you lose the \[Muted\] condition. If you gained \[Muted\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose the \[Muted\] condition.
== Off Balance

_Cause:_ When a skill action, condition, or effect makes it harder to keep your balance as you move, you are \[Off Balance\].

_Effect:_ When you move, make a basic Agility roll with a DL of Easy (6). If you fail, your move stops at the \[Half-Speed\] point, and you fall \[Prone\].

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Off Balance\] is removed, you lose the \[Off Balance\] condition.
== Off Guard

_Cause:_ When you are in a state of being unprepared for immediate danger, you are \[Off Guard\]. Most people are \[Off Guard\] by default.

_Effect:_ Attacks made against a person who is \[Off Guard\] have their DL lowered by one.

_Removal:_ When you observe immediate danger, you lose \[Off Guard\].
== Severely Wounded

_Cause:_ When you are reduced to half your half of your Wounded value (or less) in hit points, you gain the \[Severely Wounded\] condition.

_Effect:_ You gain \[Movement Impaired\]. All skill actions have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When you have more than half your Wounded value in hit points, you lose the \[Severely Wounded\] condition. You also lose the \[Severely Wounded\] condition if you advance to \[Death's Door\] or \[Dying\].
== Prone

_Cause:_ When you lay down on the ground or are forced down by a condition or an attack, you gain \[Prone\].

_Effect:_ \[Ranged\] attacks made against you, except Point Blank Shot, have their DL raised by one. \[Melee\] attacks made against you have their DL lowered by one. On your turn while \[Prone\], you may spend 1 AP to move, as if you were \[Movement Restricted\].

_Removal:_ When you stand up, you lose the \[Prone\] condition.
== Speech Impairment

_Cause:_ When a condition or effect makes it hard for you to speak, you have \[Speech Impairment\].

_Effect:_ Skill actions with the \[Vocal\] keyword have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to have a \[Speech Impairment\] is removed, you lose the \[Speech Impairment\] condition. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Stabilized

_Cause:_ When you are the target of a successful First Aid roll, or you succeed on a basic Resilience roll to avoid Dying, you gain the \[Stabilized\] condition..

_Effect:_ You lose the following conditions: \[Bleeding\], \[Critical Condition\], \[Dying\], \[Traumatized\], and \[Unconscious\].

_Removal:_ After \[Stabilized\] takes effect on you, you lose the \[Stabilized\] condition.
== Stunned

_Cause:_ When a skill action, condition or effect causes you to have a momentary mental shutdown, you are \[Stunned\].

_Effect:_ You are \[Immobilized\], \[Unaware\], and \[Incapable\].

_Removal:_ At the end of your next turn, you lose the \[Stunned\] condition.
== Suffocating

_Cause:_ When a condition or effect makes it almost impossible for you to breathe, you are \[Suffocating\].

_Effect:_ At the start of your turn, take 1 damage. You get 2 AP on your turn (instead of 3 AP). Attack rolls and rolls to use Athletics, Driving, and Stealth skill actions have their DL raised by _two_.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Suffocating\] is removed, you lose the \[Suffocating\] condition.
== Suppressed

_Cause:_ When enemy gunfire pins you down, making it harder to move and retaliate, you are \[Suppressed\]. A single target can only have one instance of \[Suppressed\] at a time. Multiple applications of \[Suppressed\] on the same target do not stack.

_Effect:_ You gain \[Movement Impaired\]. When you make an attack, the DL is raised by one.

_Removal:_ At the end of your next turn, you lose the \[Suppressed\] condition.
== Suspicious

_Cause:_ When you sense that someone may be lying, hiding something, or mispresenting the truth, you are \[Suspicious\]. This condition cannot be applied to player characters.

_Effect:_ If you have a Friendly Attitude it shifts to Neutral. Attempts to use Influence or Deception skill actions against you have their DL raised by one: If the person you are suspicious of  is using a Disguise or a Forgery, you may attempt to see through it.

_Removal:_ If the subject of your suspicions raises your Attitude to Friendly, you lose \[Suspicious\].
== Traumatized

_Cause:_ When you sustain an injury by rolling on the _Injury Severity Chart_, you gain the \[Traumatized\] condition.

_Effect:_ All skill actions have their DL is raised by one.

_Removal:_ When you are \[Stabilized\], you lose the \[Traumatized\] condition. If you are still \[Traumatized\] at the end of the current scene, you lose the \[Traumatized\] condition.
== Unaware

_Cause:_ When you gain \[Unconscious\] or \[Stunned\], you also gain \[Unaware\]. You can also be rendered \[Unaware\] by certain special attacks.

_Effect:_ You are \[Blinded\], \[Deafened\], and \[Off Guard\].

_Removal:_ When you lose \[Blinded\] or \[Deafened\], you lose \[Unaware\].
== Unconscious

_Cause:_ When you gain the \[Dying\] condition, you also gain \[Unconscious\]. You can also be rendered \[Unconscious\] by certain special attacks.

_Effect:_ You are \[Immobilized\], \[Incapable\], \[Prone\], \[Unaware\], and \[Unresponsive\].

_Removal:_ When you gain \[Stabilized\] and have at least 1 hit point, you lose the \[Unconscious\] condition.
== Undetected

_Cause:_ If a person has not detected your presence, then you are \[Undetected\] by them.

_Effect:_ When you attack a target for whom you are \[Undetected\], they are treated as \[Off Guard\] for that attack.

_Removal:_ When you are seen or heard by someone, you are no longer \[Undetected\] to them.
== Unresponsive

_Cause:_ When you gain the \[Unconscious\] condition, you also gain \[Unresponsive\]. You can also be rendered \[Unresponsive\] by certain special attacks.

_Effect:_ You are \[Muted\] and cannot communicate in any way.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused you to be \[Unresponsive\] is removed, you lose the \[Unresponsive\] condition.
== Vision Impairment

_Cause:_ When you have difficulty seeing due to a condition or injury, you have \[Vision Impairment\].

_Effect:_ Skill actions with the \[Visual\] have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When the condition that caused \[Vision Impairment\] is removed, you lose the \[Vision Impairment\] condition. If you gained \[Vision Impairment\] as the result of an injury, receiving Surgery or Cybernetic Installation, as described in the Recovery entry of the injury description. causes you to lose \[Vision Impairment\]. In rare cases, this condition is permanent.
== Wounded

_Cause:_ When you are reduced to half your maximum hit points (or less), you gain the \[Wounded\] condition. this condition follows and replaces \[Healthy\].

_Effect:_ All skill actions have their DL raised by one.

_Removal:_ When you have more than half your maximum hit points, you lose the \[Wounded\] condition. You also lose the \[Wounded\] condition if you advance to \[Seriously Wounded\], \[Death's Door\], or \[Dying\].